OL,6,FThe service is much more
OL,7,Fcomprehensive than ITV 1's equivalent
OL,8,F` three hourly bulletins of
OL,9,Fapproximately one minute's duration
OL,10,Fplus a short local weather forecast
OL,11,Fwhich would appear to be recorded the
OL,12,Fnight before, at least in some
OL,13,Fregions.
OL,15,FRegional opts were only introduced to
OL,16,FITV's breakfast programme when GMTV
OL,17,Ftook over the franchise in 1993
OL,18,Fwhereas they have been a key part of
OL,19,Fthe BBC's service since day 1 of
OL,20,FBreakfast Time.
OL,3,CBBC regional news resumes pre-
